uk.ac.ebi.pride.jmztab.utils.parser

Class MZTabHeaderLineParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ebi.pride.jmztab.utils.parser.MZTabLineParser
      • uk.ac.ebi.pride.jmztab.utils.parser.MZTabHeaderLineParser
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    PEHLineParser, PRHLineParser, PSHLineParser, SMHLineParser

    public abstract class MZTabHeaderLineParser
extends MZTabLineParser
    A couple of common method used to parse a header line into MZTabColumnFactory structure. NOTICE: MZTabColumnFactory maintain a couple of MZTabColumn which have internal logical position and order. In physical mzTab file, we allow user not obey this logical position organized way, and provide their date with own order. In order to distinguish them, we use physical position (a positive integer) to record the column location in mzTab file. And use PositionMapping structure the maintain the mapping between them.
    Since:
    11/02/13
    Author:
    qingwei
    See Also:
    PRHLineParser, PEHLineParser, PSHLineParser, SMHLineParser

        Parse a header line into MZTabColumnFactory structure. There are two steps in this method: Step 1: parseStableOrderColumns() focus on validate and parse for stable columns and optional columns which have stable order; and Step 2: parseOptionalColumns(int) focus on AbundanceColumn, OptionColumn and CVParamOptionColumn parse and validation.
